Distribution. Only known from Lizard Island. Specimens were collected twice (in
1995 and 2013
), in spite of extensive collecting for polychaetes over the last 40 years at Lizard, indicating this species is rare. The type locality is an easily accessible site which has been dived at many times by Pat Hutchings since Lizard Island Research Station was established in 1973 .
